{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb200 
In April 1976, the defendant was employed by the plaintiff, and as part of his compensation was allowed to live in a trailer house owned by plaintiff. Defendant\rquote s employment terminated June 26, 1976, but defendant continued to live in the trailer house. On July 8, 1976, defendant was served with a notice of \u8220\'3fEviction and Notice to Vacate\u8221\'3f which stated in part that defendant was to vacate immediately. On July 13, defendant was served with a summons and complaint for unlawful detainer. He vacated the trailer house on July 26. Trial was held in November 1976 and judgment entered in January of 1977. The court found that defendant was liable for rent from July 11, 1976, through July 26, 1976, and doubled the rent as provided by statute. Judgment was entered against defendant for $200 plus costs and statutory attorney\rquote s fees.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The unlawful detainer statute, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000259&cite=WAST59.12.030&originatingDoc=Iddad075af77c11d98ac8f235252e36df&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.UserEnteredCitation)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul1 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
RCW 59.12.030, et seq.
}}}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, is a special statutory procedure to determine the right to possession. 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I46235052f76411d98ac8f235252e36df&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=df932a965453428a9c36a96b653bfecd&contextData=(sc.UserEnteredCitation)" }{\fldrslt 
